This article is a statement by the President of the United States congratulating King Felipe VI on his investiture as King of Spain. The President expresses gratitude to King Juan Carlos I for his leadership and friendship in guiding Spain's democracy and strengthening the transatlantic relationship. The President emphasizes the strong ties between Spain and the United States and looks forward to working closely with King Felipe VI to further strengthen this bond. The article concludes by stating that as Spain celebrates this transition and looks to the future, the American people also celebrate along with the people of Spain.